<div id="ta187_85" class="block iDevice_content">
<div class="dentro_contenidos" style="display: block;" id="pagina_1">
<p>This task consists of a <b>multiple choice cloze</b> in which the student has to show its lexical and lexico-grammatical knowledge.</p>
<p>Students will be required to fill 12 gaps in a modified cloze using a series of items provided.</p>
<p>Tips:</p>
<ul>
<li>First, read the title and the text to have a general idea of what’s about.</li>
<li>In order to choose the right option, take into account how words are used, the meaning and the grammar connected with particular words.</li>
<li>Deal with the spaces one by one reading before and after the gap.</li>
<li>If you are not sure of which is the right alternative discard those which you think are wrong.</li>
<li>Consider the following: Is there a word which is usually used in that context? Is there a preposition which would only match one of the alternatives?</li>
<li>Finally, read the whole text again to check your answers.</li>
</ul>
